<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 1:41AM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
southeastern Surry, Stokes and southwestern Rockingham Counties
through 230 AM EDT...
At 141 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sandy Ridge, moving southeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Madison...
Pilot Mountain...
Walnut Cove...
Danbury...
Francisco...
King...
and Pine Hall.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
